# Project Rules
## Always apply

### Project Structure
- Keep models in appropriate directories
- Maintain clear separation of concerns
- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Keep scripts organized by purpose
- Maintain clear documentation structure
- Separate evaluation and training code

### Data Management
- Use appropriate data versioning
- Document data preprocessing steps
- Keep data pipeline reproducible
- Validate input data formats
- Maintain data privacy requirements
- Document data augmentation methods

### Model Management
- Version control model checkpoints
- Document model architectures
- Track experiment configurations
- Log training metrics
- Maintain model cards
- Document model limitations

### Evaluation
- Use consistent evaluation metrics
- Document evaluation procedures
- Maintain benchmark results
- Track performance regressions
- Document evaluation environment
- Keep evaluation scripts reproducible

### Dependencies
- Pin dependency versions
- Document environment setup
- Keep requirements.txt updated
- Document GPU requirements
- Maintain virtual environment
- Track dependency conflicts

### CI/CD
- Run tests before merging
- Validate configuration files
- Check code formatting
- Run security checks
- Validate documentation
- Check for memory leaks

### Documentation
- Keep README updated
- Document setup procedures
- Maintain API documentation
- Document known issues
- Keep changelog updated
- Document deployment procedures
